ENUMERATE:
enumerate() gives both index and value at the same time.
example1
NAME = "mountain"
for index, letter in enumerate(NAME):
   print(letter*(index+1))

o/p:
m
oo
uuu
nnnn
ttttt
aaaaaa
iiiiiii
nnnnnnnn

note:
1) (index+1):here we mention index+1 because if index 0 means that m letter will not display so we mention (index+1)
2) letter * (index + 1)
Repeats each letter based on its position

example2
l = [12,21,1,18,26]
for index, letter in enumerate(l):
   print(f"{letter}no is {index}th index")

